description:
Final pass: This was missed because reviewers checked the frame_len validation after lichen_link_tx, but not whether frame_len is undefined on error paths.

Root cause: At line 830:
  size_t frame_len = sizeof(tx_frame_buf);
Then at line 845:
  ret = lichen_link_tx(&link_ctx, tx_ipv6_buf, pkt_len, NULL, tx_frame_buf, &frame_len);

If lichen_link_tx() returns an error early (before modifying frame_len), frame_len retains its initial value of sizeof(tx_frame_buf) = 255. The code at line 856 then checks:
  if (frame_len > sizeof(tx_frame_buf))

This check will always pass (255 > 255 is false) even if frame_len was never actually set to a meaningful value.

This is defense-in-depth paranoia, but the check provides false confidence - it only catches lichen_link_tx writing an invalid value, not lichen_link_tx failing to write a value at all.

Fix: Zero-initialize frame_len, or skip the bounds check on error paths entirely (since we return early anyway).
